rComments: Dr. Kulik is the most fair professor I have had at university. If you have good reason to remark any assignments, he is very patient and willing to go through it with you. He is very available and his notes are always very clear. This was a great class, I would strongly recommend taking a class with Dr. Kulik if you can!
the course was difficult. Great prof. Really cares about the students. Slides could be sometimes more detailed. Two hours of office hours at midnights were a cherry on the cake.
Not too hard a class; professor's explanations were decent and the slides were well-written.
This man anit playing no games! do not cheat! he was nice and helpful, one of the best profs in the department of math.
Best prof ever
A really great prof! He cares about his students and wants them to succeed. The course material can be difficult but he explains it very well and is happy to help you in his office hours.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Excellent prof.  Always provides supplementary course notes and midterm/final reviews to help you study. Exam material is super similar to homework, and it's pretty easy to do well given you put in some effort.
Great prof, straightforward assignments/exams. Uploads practice midterms/finals that are very similar to actual exams.

Fantastic prof! All his teaching was very similar to exams and assignments, you could tell he genuinely cared about how well his students did. If you have the opportunity to take a class with him you should.

Amazing prof! Lectures are interesting and he is always willing to answer questions. He also gives study guides for the midterm and exams that tell you exactly which subjects will be on them. Would definitely take a class with him again if I have the chance!
Excellent professor. Knows the subject very well. Lectures are clear. Final exam was  similar to practice exam.
Hard to hear sometimes but his notes on the board are stellar. Exams very accurately reflect assignments and are quite easy. I would definitely take stats with him again.

Beyond me how peeps can hate on kulik. He's THE man. Recommend him for every single math class you have. He'll help you pass with flying colours, just listen to what he has to preach in class and you'll be gold. Best stats prof at the univ by far
Best statistics professor at the university. Clear, funny, and cares about you and your grades. He will help you pass with flying colours because he is very transparent with what will be tested.

Kulik is a great professor! Assignments are long but not hard.. just very tedious. He is super helpful in his office hours so make sure to see him! He's really approachable. His class notes were good and I didn't use the textbook ever. He also posts typed up lecture notes online. Midterm and exam were fair and there were no major surprises.
All over the place

Very disorganized. Not a good lecturer (although you can tell that he knows his stuff). Lecture notes are useless. The book chosen for this course is terrible and for the most part irrelevant to the material covered in class. Hence very difficult to master the material, which is disappointing because time-series analysis is very interesting :(

This guy is one of the best math profs of uOttawa. He's so helpful in his office hours, and doesn't trick us when it comes to tests. You will know exactly what to study: no surprises. He's a hard worker, and is a great teacher. I can't recommend this guy enough.A+ for him.

The guy is amazing! everything he talks about in class is on the exam so its not difficult to know what material youll be tested on. AND he gives hints on what questions to study, his exam and midterm reviews were kick-ass ! Definitely take the course with the dude and hes chil
He is a prof who seems to be all over the place. Disorganized, and horrible for giving help.  He'd rather just give you the answer in his office than help you.
Long story short: RAFAK KULIK IS THE MAN ! He was pretty funny in class and knows how to teach ! MUST TAKE HIM FOR ALL IF NOT EVERY MATH CLASS YOU HAVE

Amazing professor ! Very talented and knows how to convey the subject of matter at hand. If you attend class he covers examples that are as is right on the assigments and exam. In addition to being available during office hours, he cares about students being successful and goes out of his way just to help. Highly recommended!!
This prof is extremely smart and knowledgeable about course material. Also, Kulik goes out of his way to help you understand. Highly recommended!

Clear vocal instructions. Always listen to what he's saying. Doesn't follow manual exactly, but you get what you need from lectures. Deserves a 2/5 in clarity: he get's messy on the blackboard and sometimes doesn't finish proofs ... exams and HW are made easy (on purpose, I think).

He is an amazing professor, material presented in the class and on the exam is strongly correlated. He is available to help in office hours. Just do your assignments, practice problems and past final and you will get a good mark.
Great prof!  The material itself can get a little dry, but he tries to make it as interesting as possible.  No surprises on the final or midterm - very straight forward and simple.
Good Prof! Review assignments and sample exam and you will do good in the final.

Awesome prof. I sat in the front row, I like that he writes stuff on the board first and gives us a chance to copy, THEN explains it. It's very helpful. Exam was long but straight-forward, do-able. His accent did not bother me as my parents have the same one. Will take other classes with him as the professor, for sure.

Teaches from slides in a dark room. Painfully boring, better than a sleeping pill. Exams and assignments were very easy, though. You can get through the class without actually learning anything (I forgot most of what I learned as I walked out the door) which is a pain.

Boring prof, you can learn everything through the slides. Still though in some lectures his explanations were clear, while in others they weren't clear at all. Just beware of the final exam, a few marks lost there can change your grade level a lot.

surely this guy has to be one of the easiest professors around. midterm and finala re both multiple choice and open book. with a course like this, you can ace the course if it is open book. i barely went to class all semester...any course with this guy and ill take it!
He's extremely helpful, approachable and explains things well. His tests are super easy and so are the assignments. ANd yes, I think he's hot as well.

this class had to be the easiest class i've ever took.. and with kulic, it couldn't have been easier. i copied assignments, studied 2 hours for the midterm and 2 hours for the final, both open book of couse and ended up with an A+. half the class got at least an A-. what sucked was that ppl who got 89-89.9 were rounded to an A.

Professor Kulik is by far the one and only teacher who truly cares about the performance of his students. When asked, he addresses all the questions in a very clear and respectful manner. He deserves an award.
He cares about how his students do in his class. He's very clear and really helpful and fair. Not to mention he's a babe!

very good prof. although he has an accent, you get use to it in 3 -4 classes. Always willing to help. Jokes a few times, very nice and try hard to deliever the message across to students with many examples!
The best and easy prof than ever. His midterm and exam was dam easy, and if you just study a bit, you can good grade.

very good professor.
the poor guy is trying. I like him!!! Hes cool and sometimes funny!
british? no some kind of european heavy accent.. not that it matters u ask him a question and he sits there and blinks at you...buddy im sorry but im not one to know morse code...
